HEADWORD: Ambilevous
<hw>Am`bi*le"vous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambo</ets> both + <ets>laevus</ets> left.]</ety> <def>Left-handed
on both sides; clumsy; -- opposed to <contr>ambidexter</contr>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
